
<h3>Project Overview</h3>

<p style="font-size: 16px">
    The Schoenberg Database of Manuscripts (SDBM) contains normalized
    data records of descriptions of manuscripts gathered from various
    sources. Drawn from over 12,000 auction and sales catalogues,
    inventories, catalogues from institutional and private
    collections, and other sources, the SDBM assists in locating and
    identifying particular manuscripts, establishing provenance, and
    aggregating descriptive information.
</p>

<p style="font-size: 16px">
    The SDBM aims to be an open access, user-built, community-driven
    research tool for the history of manuscript tranmissions
    from production to the present.
</p>

