<h3>The Data Model</h3>

<p>The database contains the following primary entities:</p>

<dl class="dl-horizontal">

    <dt><b>Entries</b></dt>
    <dd>An entry describes the features of a manuscript, as recorded in
        a particular source of information.
    </dd>

    <dt><b>Sources</b></dt>
    <dd>A source of information from which an entry originates. These
        include auction catalogs, inventories, censuses, an individual
        making direct observations about manuscripts, etc.</dd>

    <dt><b>Provenance Agents</b></dt>
    <dd>A person or organization involved in the history of a
    manuscript's possession and transmission.  These include
    scriptoria, auction houses, dealers, collectors, university
        collections, etc.</dd>

    <dt><b>Names</b></dt>
    <dd>A person who is an author, a scribe, or an artist of a
    manuscript.</dd>

    <dt><b>Manuscripts</b></dt>
    <dd>A manuscript record associates entries together that refer to
    the same physical object.</dd>

</dl>

